<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890205>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 64. Dorsal, ventral, and internal views of Macroscapha inaequata (Maddocks, 1990), Macroscapha rehmi sp. nov., Macroscapha scotia sp. nov., Macroscapha turbida (Müller, 1908), and Macroscapha walterae sp. nov. Macroscapha walterae sp. nov.: A, subfossil paratype (ZMH K-41486); I, J, paratype adult male (SNB 0051, ZMH K-40818). Macroscapha turbida (Müller, 1908): B, C, adult male; D, adult female (ZMH K-41476). Macroscapha scotia sp. nov.: E, paratype adult female, F, paratype adult male (ZMH K-33192); M, N, paratype adult male (SNB 0022, ZMH K-40837). Macroscapha inaequata (Maddocks, 1990): G, H, adult female (SNB 0054, ZMH K-40819). Macroscapha rehmi sp. nov.: K, L, paratype adult female (SNB 0059, ZMH K-40836). A, B, D–F, right and left valve (RLV) dorsal view; C, RLV ventral view; G, I, K, M, LV internal view; H, J, L, N, RV internal view. Scale bar = 500 Mm. The arrows point towards the anterior of the animal." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4890205/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890152>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 37. External view of right valves of Macroscapha inaequata Maddocks, 1990, Macroscapha scotia sp. nov., and Macroscapha walterae sp. nov. Macroscapha inaequata Maddocks, 1990: A, adult female (SNB 0752, ZMH K-40821); B, adult male (SNB 0578-DNA 285. ZMH K-41487); H, (SNB 0052); I, (SNB 0053); J, adult female (SNB 0054) (ZMH 40819). Macroscapha scotia sp. nov.: C, paratype A M? (ZMH K-35501); D, holotype adult male (SNB 0739, ZMH K-40820); E, paratype adult male (SNB 0022); F, paratype adult female (SNB 0056); G, paratype adult female (SNB 0741) (ZMH K-40837). Macroscapha walterae sp. nov.: K, holotype adult male (SNB 0745, ZMH K-41484); L, paratype adult male (SNB 0051); M, paratype adult male (SNB 0750); N, paratype adult female (SNB 0048) (ZMH K-40818). Scale bar = 500 Mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4890152/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890146>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 34. Geographical distribution and height ¥ length scatter plot of valves of Macroscapha inaequalis, Macroscapha inaequata, Macroscapha walterae sp. nov., Macroscapha sp. aff. walterae sp. nov., and Macroscapha sp. (of the informal group Macroscapha turbida). Both records of Mh. inaequata (Maddocks, 1990) from the Pacific Sector of the Southern Ocean are herein considered dubious because they are based on only one female (Ross Sea) and one very large teratological adult of indeterminable sex (south-west Pacific Basin; Maddocks, 1990)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4890146/files/figure.png" .

